## 0. AWS EC2 — stop instances by tag (you already had this)

```python
import boto3

ec2 = boto3.resource("ec2")

def stop_tagged_temp_instances():
    for instance in ec2.instances.all():
        if instance.state["Name"] != "running":
            continue
        tags = instance.tags or []
        if any(t["Key"] == "temp" for t in tags):
            print(f"Stopping {instance.id}")
            instance.stop()

if __name__ == "__main__":
    stop_tagged_temp_instances()
```

**Add later:** CloudWatch `get_metric_statistics` on `CPUUtilization` before stopping.

