## 1. Log parsing — `pathlib`, `re`, read line-by-line

```python
from pathlib import Path
import re

ERROR_LINE = re.compile(r"ERROR|CRITICAL", re.I)

def scan_logs(log_dir: Path):
    for path in log_dir.glob("*.log"):
        with path.open(encoding="utf-8", errors="replace") as f:
            for i, line in enumerate(f, 1):
                if ERROR_LINE.search(line):
                    print(f"{path.name}:{i}: {line.rstrip()}")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    scan_logs(Path("/var/log/myapp"))
```

Uses **`re`** for pattern, **`pathlib`** for paths, safe encoding on bad bytes.

Same idea with **`os.walk`** (older codebases):

```python
import os
import re
pat = re.compile(r"ERROR", re.I)
for root, _, files in os.walk("/var/log/myapp"):
    for name in files:
        if not name.endswith(".log"):
            continue
        path = os.path.join(root, name)
        with open(path, encoding="utf-8", errors="replace") as f:
            for i, line in enumerate(f, 1):
                if pat.search(line):
                    print(f"{path}:{i}:{line.rstrip()}")
```

