## 5. Send email — `smtplib` + `email` (stdlib)

```python
import smtplib
from email.mime.text import MIMEText

def send_plain_alert(
    smtp_host: str,
    smtp_port: int,
    user: str,
    password: str,
    mail_from: str,
    mail_to: str,
    subject: str,
    body: str,
):
    msg = MIMEText(body)
    msg["Subject"] = subject
    msg["From"] = mail_from
    msg["To"] = mail_to

    with smtplib.SMTP(smtp_host, smtp_port) as smtp:
        smtp.starttls()
        smtp.login(user, password)
        smtp.sendmail(mail_from, [mail_to], msg.as_string())

# send_plain_alert("smtp.gmail.com", 587, "...", "...", "from@x.com", "to@x.com", "Alert", "Disk full on host1")
```

Use **secrets** from env or Vault — never hard-code passwords in repo.

