## Bonus — Tiny Flask app — HTTP endpoint (`pip install flask`)

```python
# pip install flask
from flask import Flask, request, jsonify

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.get("/health")
def health():
    return jsonify(status="ok"), 200

@app.post("/echo")
def echo():
    data = request.get_json(force=True, silent=False)
    return jsonify(you_sent=data), 200

if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run(host="0.0.0.0", port=5000)
```

**Interview line:** Flask for **small internal tools** (health, admin hooks); production often uses **gunicorn** + reverse proxy.

